n and groups. The Solidarity Encounter concludes by offering strategies for respecting boundaries between self and other, providing a constructive framework for non-colonizing solidarity that can be applied in any context of unequal power.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIndigenous womenxPolitical activityzCanada. 0aMinority women activistszCanada. 0aReconciliationzCanada. 0aSocial movementszCanada. 0aSolidarityzCanada. 0aWomen political activistszCanada. 0aWomen, WhitexPolitical activityzCanada. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Race & Ethnic Relations.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311141763940uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486440440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774864404423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774864404/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-141763-9  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles